civitatem] The Socii claimed the Roman Civitas, which was granted after a hard con- test. See Lex Julia de Civitate, Vol. ii. Index.

Sulla cum Scipione] L. Cornelius Scipio was consul in B.c. 83, in the beginning of which year Sulla returned to Italy from the east. He had a conference with Scipio, whose troops betrayed him and went over to Sulla.
